{"word":"γνήσιος","slug":"γνήσιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>γνήσιος, α, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γένος\">γένος</a></el> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γίνομαι\">γίνομαι</a></el>; ‘belonging to ancestral stock’, hence ‘legitimate’] <b><i>true</i> <a href='B:570 4:3'>Phil 4:3</a>; <a href='B:610 1:2'>1 Ti 1:2</a>; <a href='B:630 1:4'>Tit 1:4</a>.</b> As noun <el>τὸ γνήσιον</el>, suggesting a characteristic that is inborn <b><i>genuineness, quality, sincerity,</i> <a href='B:540 8:8'>2 Cor 8:8</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:γναφεύς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:γνησίως\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}